						               													<description>The game contains card in two colors, each color has 4 creatures printed on them, the same creatures for each color.  Both colors have 24 cards, each creature has 6 cards in both colors.  There are 48 players card, 6 advanced assignments cards and 1 rule card, making a total of 55 cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players pick one of either color (blue or red) and take all cards in that color and shuffle them up.  They then take turns playing a card, adding it to the set, either horizontally or vertically, but not diagonally.  Their goal is to make a set of 4 cards, either horizontally, vertically or diagonally, of their own color.  The type of monster is not important, only that it's your color.  This can also be played to get 4 in a row, with the rules unchanged otherwise.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is an advanced version of the game, this uses the 6 advanced assignment cards, where you have to place your monsters in a specific shape to win.  This also includes a &amp;quot;X * monster&amp;quot; card, which means you only win if you get 4 monster (or 5 in the 5-in-a-row variant) in the same row.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game resembles a paper version of a 4/5-in-a-row type Tic-Tac-Toe game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game was published as part of a promotional campaign for the KFC restaurant group.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
